               <msContents class="#multipleWorks">
                  <summary>A composite volume of five short works by Bahá'u'lláh: the
                     Ṣaḥífa-i-Mubáraka-i-Fársiyya ("Blessed Persian Epistle"), the
                     Kalimát-i-Firdawsiyya ("Words of Paradise"), the Ṭirázát ("Ornaments"), the
                     Tajalliyát ("Effulgences"), and the (true) Lawḥ-i-Aqdas. Sent in place of the
                     "Hidden Words," which had been requested but were not yet ready (see <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_603">F. 33 (BBA.
                        4)</ref>).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_32-item1" n="1">
                     <locus from="2b" to="48a">ff. 2b-48a</locus>
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh, 1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_394">Ṣaḥāʼif pārisīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_394">صحائف پارسية</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_394">Ṣaḥífa-i-Mubáraka-i-Fársiyya (Blessed Persian Epistle)</title>
                     <note>A note on f. 1a states this Epistle was revealed in answer to a
                        question addressed to "the Supreme Purity" (Bahá'u'lláh) about the "Hidden
                        Book of Fáṭima." Despite the note's description of it as Persian, Browne
                        observes that more than half (ff. 2b-27b) is in fact in Arabic; the
                        Persian portion begins on f. 27b, l. 3.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">هذه صحیفة الله المهیمن
                        القیوم هو الله تعالی شأنه الحکمة و البیان... (f. 2b)</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">... اهل ایران از حافظ و
                        معین گذشته‌اند... (ff. 47b-48b)</explicit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/95">p.69</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBA. 3</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892): 637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_32-item2" n="2">
                     <locus from="48a" to="64a">ff. 48a-64a</locus>
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh, 1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_395">Kalimāt firdawsīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_395">كلمات فردوسية</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_395">Kalimát-i-Firdawsiyya (Words of Paradise)</title>
                     <note>Title and opening words written obliquely in the margin, in red.
                        Arranged in ten "leaves" (waraq), the tenth considerably longer than the
                        rest.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">کلمات فردوسیه کلمة الله در
                        ورق آل فردوس اعلی از قلم ابهی مذکور و مسطور...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa" defective="true"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/95">p.69</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBA. 3</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892): 637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_32-item3" n="3">
                     <locus from="66a" to="77a">ff. 66a-77a (approximate)</locus>
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh, 1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_396">Ṭirāzāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_396">طرازات</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_396">Ṭirázát (Ornaments)</title>
                     <note>Six Ṭiráz ("ornament") sections; the first begins on f. 66a.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">بسمی المهیمن علی الاسماء
                        حمد و ثنا مالک اسماء و فاطر اسما را لایق و سزاست...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa" defective="true"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/95">p.69</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBA. 3</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892): 637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, with an Arabic exordium</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_32-item4" n="4">
                     <locus from="77b" to="84b">ff. 77b-84b</locus>
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh, 1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_397">Tajallīyāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_397">تجليات</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_397">Tajalliyát (Effulgences)</title>
                     <note>Four Tajallís ("effulgences"); the first begins on f. 80b.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">هو الساطع من افقه الاعلی
                        شهد الله انه لا اله الا هو...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/95">p.69</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBA. 3</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892): 637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_32-item5" n="5">
                     <locus from="85a" to="94b">ff. 85a-94b</locus>
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh, 1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_398">Lawḥ-i aqdas</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_398">لوح اقدس</title>
                     <note>Browne distinguishes this, "the real Lawḥ-i-Aqdas," from the
                        Kitáb-i-Aqdas he had earlier (mistakenly, as he explains at BBP. 3) called
                        by this name. He notes a passage near the end confirms information he had
                        earlier given Baron Rosen: that this Tablet was addressed to a Christian.
                        Ends without colophon on f. 94b.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">هذا اللوح الاقدس نزل من
                        الملکوت الاقدس لمن اقبل الی قبلة العالم... (f. 85a)</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">... طوبی لمن انقطع عن...
                        و شرب کوثر فضلی... (f. 94b)</explicit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/95">p.69</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBA. 3</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892): 637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
